latestPosts.caption:
Well, here we are in the last hour of your special day—and I’m keeping the promise I made to myself: to always write a little something for you on your birthday. Sure, we live under the same roof, and I could just come and say it all out loud… but I want this here, written down, forever. A little memory tucked into time.

Let’s rewind to the morning—me, cranky as ever, picking a fight with all the grace of a sleepy cat. You, smiling through it, dodging every jab with kindness, and then somehow making it better by saying the simplest thing: “You’re a good person.” And just like that, you disarmed my mood.

We spent the day roaming the streets, hunting for pieces of dreams like they were hidden in corners. And when the sun dipped, I had my moments again—ready to stir the pot—but you held your calm, like you always do. And here I am, choosing to write instead of say all this because I want it remembered, not just heard.

You have this quiet magic about you—turning regular days into beautiful ones, and people into better versions of themselves, just by being you. You’ve done that to me more times than I can count.

I’m so ridiculously lucky to have you—the dream-chaser, the never-gives-up kind of human, the one who will break every wall down to make a window. You’re tough when life needs it, soft when love does, and always, always true to who you are.

I am thanking God and mum for bringing someone like you into this world—and into mine.

I love you, deeply. 

Happy birthday.

Yours—always,

latestPosts.caption:
The beauty of a perfect picture lies in the silent dance between the one behind the lens and the one in front. 

It was a peaceful morning in Anech, Himachal Pradesh. I woke up early, craving that fresh mountain air and warm sunshine. With my morning ritual of tea, he picked up the camera and captured these moments. It wasn’t planned, but special.

For most of my life, I’ve been camera-shy, uncomfortable with being in front of it. But here I am, feeling at ease, simply because of how he makes me feel and how much he loves taking picture of me. It reminded me of something important: it’s not just about the picture, it’s about the people who choose you everyday. ♥️
